    <text xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
        <body>
            <head>251. Memorandum From the Special Assistant to the Deputy Secretary of State
                    (<persName corresp="recoqpx2aNuHTDUHK">Timbie</persName>) to Secretary of State
                    <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">Shultz</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d251fn1">Source: Department of State,
                    Bureau of Arms Control and Disarmament, Lot 01D127, 1969–1990 Subject Records of
                        <persName corresp="recoqpx2aNuHTDUHK">James P. Timbie</persName>, Box 1,
                        <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_INF_1"
                        >INF</gloss> 1987. Secret.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                        calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1987-12-10T08:00:00-05:00"
                        notBefore="1987-12-10T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Mr. Secretary:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Attached are materials for your meeting with <persName corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc"
                    >Shevardnadze</persName> this morning:</p>
            <p>1. <hi rendition="simple_italic">The draft <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recHvtjt4uCqCi2Qk">START</rs>
                    </gloss> Text</hi>.<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d251fn2">Attached but not
                    printed. See Attachment, <ref target="#d250">Document 250</ref>.</note> It is
                quite good, and incorporates real advances in <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="reclksm3VX3UUxetF">throwweight</rs>, <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recr08QgEMEm1Bk04">ballistic missile</rs>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warhead</rs>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="recTaee7UxoGjTDrc">counting rules</rs>, and <rs
                    type="topic" corresp="recXyi0y36LV93Itc">telemetry encryption</rs>. <persName
                    corresp="recIjriLJ5q37CiAe">Akhromeyev</persName> says he will give us an answer
                on one bracket in the <gloss target="#t_ALCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="rec3r8I0hO6jAW3Fm" type="topic">ALCM</rs>
                </gloss>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="recTaee7UxoGjTDrc">counting rule</rs> (“nuclear-armed”) in
                the morning, and give us the Soviet <rs corresp="recnGcR0g6J7yKHTE" type="topic"
                    >SLBM</rs>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warhead</rs> numbers at the same time.
                If <persName corresp="recIjriLJ5q37CiAe">Akhromeyev</persName> removes the bracket,
                this will represent another major step toward our position.</p>
            <p>Unfortunately, after we saw you last night <persName corresp="recIjriLJ5q37CiAe"
                    >Akhromeyev</persName> added a phrase to the <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCM</rs>
                </gloss> paragraph which we bracketed. It commits the sides to establish ceilings on
                    <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCMs</rs>
                </gloss>, and confine them to certain classes of ships. In our view, the unbracketed
                language committing us to seek effective methods of <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45"
                    type="topic">verification</rs> of <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCM</rs>
                </gloss> limits is as far as we can go at this time, and we cannot commit to limits
                until the <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs> is in hand.
                    <persName corresp="recIjriLJ5q37CiAe">Akhromeyev</persName> says there will be
                no <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recHvtjt4uCqCi2Qk">START</rs>
                </gloss> agreement without <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCM</rs>
                </gloss> constraints, so he would recommend against the <gloss target="#t_START_1"
                    >START</gloss> statement if the bracketed sentence is not included.</p>
            <p>The guidance in the NSDD is to seek Soviet views on how <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCM</rs>
                </gloss> limits could be verified, which we have done. <persName
                    corresp="recgt3SoCfObWa7Tt">Colin</persName> planned to take this subject up
                with the <orgName corresp="recYt5V8hImTp3Aah">Chiefs</orgName>, and you might touch
                base with him before you see <persName corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc"
                    >Shevardnadze</persName>. <persName corresp="recIjriLJ5q37CiAe"
                    >Akhromeyev</persName> will be seeing <persName corresp="recusSiT3UbixAWkn"
                    >Crowe</persName> in the morning, and their conversation could be helpful.</p>
            <p>Points to make:</p>
            <p>—We have studied <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic">verification</rs> of
                    <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCM</rs>
                </gloss> limits.</p>
            <p>—Have not found anything that would give us confidence.</p>
            <pb facs="1154" n="1127" xml:id="pg_1127"/>
            <p>—Therefore cannot commit to limits on <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCMs</rs>
                </gloss>.</p>
            <p>—We have agreed to take another look at the <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45"
                    type="topic">verification</rs> question.</p>
            <p>—Let’s see what we come up with. If we find something, we can revisit this issue.</p>
            <p>2. <hi rendition="simple_italic">The <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> Issues
                    Sheet</hi>
                <note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d251fn3">Attached but not printed.</note>
            </p>
            <p>3. <hi rendition="simple_italic">The draft <rs type="event"
                        corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs> Text</hi>.<note n="4"
                    place="foot" xml:id="d251fn4">Attached but not printed.</note> There are a
                number of brackets. The Working Group could have dropped the pair of brackets
                dealing with what happens after the period, and the two bracketed unilateral
                statements on conduct during the period. They have been left in to give you a basis
                for discussing these two subjects with <persName corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc"
                    >Shevardnadze</persName> and making clear to him our position, and give you an
                opportunity to work in <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">Gorbachev</persName>’s
                comment about the sides being free to do what they please after the period. (We do
                not have access to the <gloss target="#t_MEMCON_1">memcons</gloss> tonight, so we
                don’t have the language <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">Gorbachev</persName>
                used.) Whenever you wish, you can drop all the brackets except the first. If you
                want to capture the thought of the “as required” sentence, these words can be added
                to the first sentence. (The package includes both a clean copy and a markup
                    <persName corresp="rec3WaAgwEDeqcFLV">Bob Linhard</persName> has done for
                    <persName corresp="recgt3SoCfObWa7Tt">Colin</persName>.)</p>
            <p>The first bracket is the hard one. The Soviets will not want to back away from the
                October 30 language (“observance of and <rs type="compound-subject"
                    corresp="recXrGW53dEgm0PM4">non-withdrawal</rs> from the <gloss
                    target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9">Treaty</rs> for an
                agreed period”). The language in the bracket moves away from <rs
                    type="compound-subject" corresp="recXrGW53dEgm0PM4">non-withdrawal</rs> toward
                non-deployment, the direction we want to go. There will be much unhappiness if the
                qualification in the first bracket were dropped. (Conversely, <persName
                    corresp="recTyVVS5UdJjYopp">Karpov</persName> suggested dropping <hi
                    rendition="simple_italic">all</hi> the bracketed language, and you may hear that
                again.)</p>
            <p>4. <hi rendition="simple_italic">The <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N"
                        >Defense and Space</rs> Issues Sheet</hi>.</p>
            <p>5. <hi rendition="simple_italic">The October 30 Joint Announcement</hi>
                <note n="5" place="foot" xml:id="d251fn5">Attached but not printed.</note>
            </p>
            <pb facs="1155" n="1128" xml:id="pg_1128"/>
            <frus:attachment xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
                <note>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Attachment</hi>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Paper Prepared in the <orgName
                            corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">Department of State</orgName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="6" place="foot" xml:id="d251fn6">No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1987-12-10">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs>
                </p>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">1.</hi> Form of Agreement</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Separate treaty.</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: In <gloss
                                    target="#t_START_1">
                                    <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recHvtjt4uCqCi2Qk"
                                        >START</rs>
                                </gloss> Treaty or protocol to <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                                    <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recHvtjt4uCqCi2Qk"
                                        >START</rs>
                                </gloss> or <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                                <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9"
                                    >Treaty</rs>.</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">2.</hi> Nature of Commitment</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Not to <rs type="compound-subject"
                                    corresp="recXrGW53dEgm0PM4">withdraw</rs> to deploy for a
                                specified period of time.</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: Not to <rs
                                    type="compound-subject" corresp="recXrGW53dEgm0PM4"
                                    >withdraw</rs> for a specified period of time.</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">3.</hi> After the Period</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Free to deploy on 6-months’ notice.</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: <gloss target="#t_ABM_1"
                                    >ABM</gloss>
                                <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9"
                                    >Treaty</rs> continues in effect (6-months’ notice to <rs
                                    type="compound-subject" corresp="recXrGW53dEgm0PM4"
                                    >withdraw</rs>).</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">4.</hi> During the Period</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Right to pursue <rs type="topic"
                                    corresp="recJclekZAp3yKmD5">research</rs>, development and <rs
                                    type="compound-subject" corresp="recFUg0jqFk2tUZ15">testing</rs>
                                as required.</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: <rs
                                    corresp="recMjLDCnI9cLa32M" type="topic">Compliance</rs> with
                                the <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                                <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9"
                                    >Treaty</rs> as it was signed and ratified in 1972. Can be
                                accompanied by a list of devices (and characteristics); tests in
                                space of devices below agreed parameters permitted.</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">5.</hi> Form of Commitment</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Limited to <rs type="compound-subject"
                                    corresp="recXrGW53dEgm0PM4">nonwithdrawal</rs> to deploy</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: Blanket commitment</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">6.</hi> Offense/Defense</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Failure to implement <gloss
                                    target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>
                                <rs type="topic" corresp="recHoFOsQcM4e5M4k">reductions</rs> grounds
                                for termination of <gloss target="#t_DS_1">
                                    <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">D&amp;S</rs>
                                </gloss> Treaty and <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                                <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9"
                                    >Treaty</rs>.</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: Practical steps to create
                                nationwide <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recKKNyP9NHSwF6fs"
                                    >defense</rs> or other evident breach frees other side from
                                    <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>
                                <rs type="topic" corresp="recHoFOsQcM4e5M4k">reductions</rs>.</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <pb facs="1156" n="1129" xml:id="pg_1129"/>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">7.</hi> Predictability and Confidence in
                    Non-Deployment</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Exchange of data and briefings, observation
                                of tests and visits to <rs type="topic" corresp="recJclekZAp3yKmD5"
                                    >research</rs> facilities.</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>:</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">8.</hi> Further Negotiations</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US:</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: After completion of 50%
                                    <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>
                                <rs type="topic" corresp="recHoFOsQcM4e5M4k">reductions</rs>, 2–3
                                years before 10-year period expires, negotiations begin on future
                                commitments.</hi>
                        </cell>
